<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott Laboratories and

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Condensed Consolidated Statement of Cash Flows</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

  </td>

 <tr>
  <td width="70%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:70.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.0pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Cash
  Flow From (Used in) Operating Activities:</font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott Laboratories and Subsidiaries</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 1 &#151; Basis of
Presentation</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The accompanying
unaudited, condensed consolidated financial statements have been prepared
pursuant to rules&nbsp;and regulations of the Securities and Exchange
Commission and, therefore, do not include all information and footnote
disclosures normally included in audited financial statements.&#160; However, in the opinion of management, all
adjustments (which include only normal adjustments) necessary to present fairly
the results of operations, financial position and cash flows have been
made.&#160; It is suggested that these
statements be read in conjunction with the financial statements included in
Abbott&#146;s Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31,
2009.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 2 &#151; Supplemental
Financial Information</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Unvested
restricted stock units that contain non-forfeitable rights to dividends are
treated as participating securities and are included in the computation of
earnings per share under the two-class method.&#160;
Under the two-class method, net earnings are allocated between common
shares and participating securities.&#160; Net
earnings allocated to common shares for the three months ended March&nbsp;31,
2010 and 2009 were $1.001 billion and $1.436 billion, respectively.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other (income)
expense, net, for the first quarter of 2009 includes the derecognition of a
contingent liability of $797 million and ongoing contractual payments from
Takeda associated with the conclusion of the TAP joint venture, and income from
the recording of certain investments at fair value in connection with business
acquisitions.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net foreign
exchange loss (gain) includes a charge of approximately $86 million for the
impact of the devaluation of the bolivar currency in Venezuela on balance sheet
translation.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other, net in Net
cash from operating activities for 2010 and 2009 includes the effects of
contributions to defined benefit plans of $466 million and $741 million,
respectively, and to the post-employment medical and dental benefit plans of
$66 million and $13 million, respectively.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The judgment entered by
the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas against Abbott in its
litigation with New York University and Centocor,&nbsp;Inc. requires Abbott to
secure the judgment in the event that its appeal to the Federal Circuit court
is unsuccessful in overturning the district court&#146;s decision.&#160; In the first quarter of 2010, Abbott
deposited $1.87 billion with an escrow agent and considers these assets to be
restricted.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The components of
long-term investments as of March&nbsp;31, 2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009 are
as follows:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 3 &#151; Taxes on
Earnings</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Taxes on earnings reflect
the estimated annual effective rates and include charges for interest and
penalties. The effective tax rates are less than the statutory U.S. federal
income tax rate principally due to the benefit of lower statutory tax rates and
tax exemptions in several foreign taxing jurisdictions.&#160; As a result of the Patient Protection and
Affordable Care Act and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act which
were signed into law in the first quarter of 2010, Abbott recorded a charge of
approximately $60 million in the first quarter 2010 to reduce deferred tax
assets associated with retiree health care liabilities related to the Medicare Part&nbsp;D
retiree drug subsidy.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5<a name="PB_5_075306_2897"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='5',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-01.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:57 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 4 &#151;
Litigation and Environmental Matters</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott has been identified as a potentially
responsible party for investigation and cleanup costs at a number of locations
in the United States and Puerto Rico under federal and state remediation laws
and is investigating potential contamination at a number of company-owned
locations.&#160; Abbott has recorded an
estimated cleanup cost for each site for which management believes Abbott has a
probable loss exposure.&#160; No individual
site cleanup exposure is expected to exceed $3&nbsp;million, and the aggregate
cleanup exposure is not expected to exceed $15&nbsp;million.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There are a number of
patent disputes with third parties who claim Abbott&#146;s products infringe their
patents.&nbsp; In April&nbsp;2007, New York University (NYU) and Centocor,&nbsp;Inc.
filed a lawsuit in the Eastern District of Texas asserting that <i>HUMIRA</i> infringes a patent co-owned by NYU
and Centocor and exclusively licensed to Centocor.&#160; In June&nbsp;2009, a jury found that Abbott
had willfully infringed the patent and awarded NYU and Centocor approximately
$1.67 billion in past compensatory damages.&#160;
In October&nbsp;2009, the district court overturned the jury&#146;s finding
that Abbott&#146;s infringement was willful, but denied Abbott&#146;s request to overturn
the jury&#146;s verdict on validity, infringement, and damages.&#160; In December&nbsp;2009, the district court
issued a final judgment and awarded the plaintiffs an additional $175 million
in prejudgment interest.&#160; Abbott has
appealed the jury&#146;s verdict.&#160; Abbott is confident
in the merits of its case and believes that it will prevail on appeal.&#160; As a result, no reserves have been recorded
in this case.&#160; Abbott&#146;s acquisition of
Kos Pharmaceuticals Inc. resulted in the assumption of various cases and
investigations and Abbott has recorded a reserve.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There are several civil
actions pending brought by individuals or entities that allege generally that
Abbott and numerous pharmaceutical companies reported false or misleading
pricing information relating to the average wholesale price of certain
pharmaceutical products in connection with federal, state and private
reimbursement.&#160; Civil actions have also
been brought against Abbott, and in some cases other members of the
pharmaceutical industry, by state attorneys general seeking to recover alleged
damages on behalf of state Medicaid programs.&#160;
In May&nbsp;2006, Abbott was notified that the U.S. Department of
Justice intervened in a civil whistle-blower lawsuit alleging that Abbott
inflated prices for Medicaid and Medicare reimbursable drugs.&#160; Abbott has settled a few of the cases and
recorded reserves for its estimated losses in a few other cases, however,
Abbott is unable to estimate the range or amount of possible loss for the
remaining cases, and no loss reserves have been recorded for them.&#160; Many of the products involved in these cases
are Hospira products.&#160; Hospira, Abbott&#146;s
former hospital products business, was spun off to Abbott&#146;s shareholders in
2004. Abbott retained liability for losses that result from these cases and investigations
to the extent any such losses both relate to the sale of Hospira&#146;s products
prior to the spin-off of Hospira and relate to allegations that were made in
such pending and future cases and investigations that were the same as
allegations existing at the date of the spin-off.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Within the next year, legal proceedings may
occur that may result in a change in the estimated reserves recorded by
Abbott.&nbsp; For its legal proceedings and environmental exposures, except as
noted above, Abbott estimates the range of possible loss to be from
approximately $190 million to $315 million.&#160;
The recorded reserve balance at March&nbsp;31, 2010 for these
proceedings and exposures was approximately $235 million.&#160; These reserves represent management&#146;s best
estimate of probable loss, as defined by </font><font color="black" style="color:windowtext;">FASB ASC No.&nbsp;450,
&#147;Contingencies.&#148;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">While it is not
feasible to predict the outcome of all such proceedings and exposures with
certainty, management believes that their ultimate disposition should not have
a material adverse effect on Abbott&#146;s financial position, cash flows, or
results of operations, except for the cases and investigations discussed in the
third paragraph and the patent case discussed in the second paragraph of this
footnote, the resolution of which could be material to cash flows or results of
operations.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6<a name="PB_6_075327_3020"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 5 &#151;
Post-Employment Benefits</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Retirement plans consist of defined benefit,
defined contribution, and medical and dental plans.&#160; Net cost for the three months ended March&nbsp;31
for Abbott&#146;s major defined benefit plans and post-employment medical and dental
benefit plans is as follows:</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">
  <p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">
  <p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  </td>

  </td>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">45</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott funds its domestic defined benefit
plans according to IRS funding limitations.&#160;
In the first quarters of 2010 and 2009, $466 million and $741 million,
respectively, was contributed to defined benefit plans and $66 million and $13
million, respectively, was contributed to the post-employment medical and
dental benefit plans.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7<a name="PB_7_080420_141"></a></font></p>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='7',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-03.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:58 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 7 &#151; Segment
Information</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s principal
business is the discovery, development, manufacture and sale of a broad line of
health care products.&#160; Abbott&#146;s products
are generally sold directly to retailers, wholesalers, hospitals, health care
facilities, laboratories, physicians&#146; offices and government agencies
throughout the world.&#160; Abbott&#146;s
reportable segments are as follows:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Pharmaceutical
Products</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;"> &#151;
Worldwide sales of a broad line of pharmaceuticals.&#160; For segment reporting purposes, three
pharmaceutical divisions are aggregated and reported as the Pharmaceutical
Products segment.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Nutritional
Products</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;"> &#151;
Worldwide sales of a broad line of adult and pediatric nutritional products.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Diagnostic
Products</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;"> &#151;
Worldwide sales of diagnostic systems and tests for blood banks, hospitals,
commercial laboratories and alternate-care testing sites.&#160; For segment reporting purposes, three
diagnostic divisions are aggregated and reported as the Diagnostic Products
segment.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Vascular</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">  <i>Products</i>&nbsp;&#151;
Worldwide sales of coronary, endovascular, vessel closure and other products.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s underlying
accounting records are maintained on a legal entity basis for government and
public reporting requirements.&#160; Segment
disclosures are on a performance basis consistent with internal management
reporting.&#160; Intersegment transfers of
inventory are recorded at standard cost and are not a measure of segment
operating earnings.&#160; The cost of some
corporate functions and the cost of certain employee benefits are charged to
segments at predetermined rates that approximate cost.&#160; Remaining costs, if any, are not allocated to
segments. <b>&#160;</b>For acquisitions prior to 2006,
substantially all intangible assets and related amortization are not allocated
to segments.<b>&#160;
</b>The following segment information has been prepared in
accordance with the internal accounting policies of Abbott, as described above,
and are not presented in accordance with generally accepted accounting
principles applied to the consolidated financial statements.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Approximately 40 to 45 percent of the annual net cost
of share-based awards will typically be recognized in the first quarter due to
the timing of the granting of share-based awards.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other, net, for the three months ended March&nbsp;31,
2009, includes the derecognition of a contingent liability of approximately
$797 established in connection with the conclusion of the TAP joint venture.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">8<a name="PB_8_080816_7608"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 8 &#151; Incentive Stock
Programs</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In the first three months
of 2010, Abbott granted 1,510,300 stock options, 163,395 replacement stock
options, 1,734,700 restricted stock awards and 5,611,368 restricted stock units
under these programs.&#160; At March&nbsp;31,
2010, approximately 200&nbsp;million shares were reserved for future
grants.&#160; Information regarding the number
of options outstanding and exercisable at March&nbsp;31, 2010 is as follows:</font></p>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">435</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.26%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.3%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="14%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:14.36%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">435</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.3%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The total
unrecognized share-based compensation cost at March&nbsp;31, 2010 amounted to
approximately $450 million which is expected to be recognized over the next
three years.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 9 &#151; Business
Acquisitions</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2010,
Abbott acquired Solvay&#146;s pharmaceuticals business (Solvay Pharmaceuticals) for
approximately $6.1 billion, in cash, plus additional payments of up to EUR 100
million per year if certain sales milestones are met in 2011, 2012 and
2013.&#160; Contingent consideration of
approximately $290 million was recorded based on a preliminary valuation.&#160;&#160; The acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals
provides Abbott with a large and complementary portfolio of pharmaceutical
products and expands Abbott&#146;s presence in key global emerging markets.&#160; Abbott acquired control of this business on February&nbsp;15,
2010 and the financial results of the acquired operations are included in these
financial statements beginning on that date.&#160;
Net sales and pretax loss of the acquired operations, including
acquisition and integration expenses, for the first quarter 2010 were
approximately $210 million and $37 million, respectively.&#160; The acquisition was funded with current cash
and short-term investments.&#160; The
preliminary allocation of the fair value of the acquisition is shown in the
table below <i>(in billions of dollars)</i>.&nbsp;
The allocation of the fair value of the acquisition will be finalized when the
valuations are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquired intangible
assets consist primarily of product rights for currently marketed products and
will be amortized over 2 to 14 years (average of 11 years).&#160; Acquired in-process research and development
will be accounted for as indefinite lived intangible assets until regulatory
approval or discontinuation.&#160; The net
tangible assets acquired consist primarily of trade accounts receivable of
approximately $620 million, inventory of approximately $420 million, property
and equipment of approximately $710 million, net of assumed liabilities,
primarily trade accounts payable, accrued compensation and other liabilities.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following unaudited
pro forma financial information reflects the consolidated results of operations
of Abbott as if the acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals had taken place on January&nbsp;1,
2010 and January&nbsp;1, 2009.&#160; The pro
forma information includes adjustments for amortization of intangible assets
and fair value adjustments to acquisition-date inventory as well as acquisition
and integration expenses.&#160; The pro forma
financial information is not necessarily indicative of the results of
operations as they would have been had the transaction been effected on the
assumed date. (<i>in billions of dollars,
except per share amounts</i>)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  earnings per common share</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.76%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="18%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:18.0%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">0.63</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.76%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="18%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:18.0%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">0.86</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.48%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">9<a name="PB_9_081141_8146"></a></font></p>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='9',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-03.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:58 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In March&nbsp;2010, Abbott
acquired STARLIMS Technologies for approximately $105&nbsp;million, in cash,
net of cash held by STARLIMS, providing Abbott with leading products and
expertise to build its position in laboratory informatics.&#160;&#160; A substantial portion of the fair value of
the acquisition has been allocated to amortizable intangible assets and
goodwill.&#160; The allocation of the fair
value of the acquisition will be finalized when the valuation is completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On April&nbsp;20, 2010,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Facet Biotech Corporation for
approximately $430 million, in cash, net of cash held by Facet.&#160;&#160; The acquisition enhances Abbott&#146;s early- and
mid-stage pharmaceutical pipeline, including a biologic for multiple sclerosis
and compounds that complement Abbott&#146;s oncology program.&#160; A substantial portion of the fair value of
the acquisition will be allocated to acquired in-process research and
development that will be accounted for as an indefinite-lived intangible asset
until regulatory approval or discontinuation.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.
(AMO) for approximately $1.4&nbsp;billion in cash, net of cash held by AMO.
Prior to the acquisition, Abbott held a small investment in AMO. Abbott
acquired AMO to take advantage of increasing demand for vision care
technologies due to population growth and demographic shifts and AMO&#146;s premier
position in its field. Abbott acquired control of this business on February&nbsp;25,
2009 and the financial results of the acquired operations are included in these
financial statements beginning on that date. The acquisition was financed with
long-term debt. The allocation of the fair value of the acquisition is shown in
the table below: (<i>dollars in billions</i>)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.4</font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquired intangible
assets consist of established customer relationships, developed technology and
trade names and are amortized over 2 to 30&nbsp;years (average of
15&nbsp;years). Acquired in-process research and development is accounted for
as an indefinite-lived intangible asset until regulatory approval or
discontinuation. The net tangible assets acquired consist primarily of trade
accounts receivable, inventory, property and equipment and other assets, net of
assumed liabilities, primarily trade accounts payable, accrued compensation and
other liabilities. In addition, subsequent to the acquisition, Abbott repaid
substantially all of the acquired debt of AMO.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In January&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired Ibis Biosciences,&nbsp;Inc. (Ibis) for $175&nbsp;million, in
cash, to expand Abbott&#146;s position in molecular diagnostics for infectious
disease. Including a $40&nbsp;million investment in Ibis in 2008, Abbott
acquired 100&nbsp;percent of the outstanding shares of Ibis. A substantial
portion of the fair value of the acquisition has been allocated to goodwill and
amortizable intangible assets, and acquired in-process research and development
that will be accounted for as an indefinite-lived intangible asset until
regulatory approval or discontinuation. The investment in Ibis in 2008 resulted
in a charge to acquired in-process research and development. In connection with
the acquisition, the carrying amount of this investment was revalued to fair
value resulting in recording $33&nbsp;million of income, which is reported as
Other (income) expense, net.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The allocation of the
fair value of the 2009 acquisitions of Visiogen,&nbsp;Inc. and Evalve,&nbsp;Inc.
will be completed when the valuations are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Except for the
acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals, had the above acquisitions taken place
on January&nbsp;1 of the previous year, consolidated net sales and income would
not have been significantly different from reported amounts.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10<a name="PB_10_081302_7091"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='10',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-03.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:58 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 10 &#151;
Financial Instruments, Derivatives and Fair Value Measures</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certain Abbott foreign
subsidiaries enter into foreign currency forward exchange contracts to manage
exposures to changes in foreign exchange rates for anticipated intercompany
purchases by those subsidiaries whose functional currencies are not the U.S.
dollar.&#160; These contracts, totaling $1.3
billion and $2.0 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009,
respectively, are designated as cash flow hedges of the variability of the cash
flows due to changes in foreign exchange rates and are recorded at fair value.<b>&#160; </b>Accumulated
gains and losses as of March&nbsp;31, 2010 will be included in Cost of products
sold at the time the products are sold, generally through the next twelve
months.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott enters into foreign currency forward
exchange contracts to manage currency exposures for foreign currency
denominated third-party trade payables and receivables, and for intercompany
loans and trade accounts payable where the receivable or payable is denominated
in a currency other than the functional currency of the entity.&#160; For intercompany loans, the contracts require
Abbott to sell or buy foreign currencies, primarily European currencies and Japanese
yen, in exchange for primarily U.S. dollars and other European currencies.&#160; For intercompany and trade payables and
receivables, the currency exposures are primarily the U.S. dollar, European
currencies and Japanese yen.&#160; At March&nbsp;31,
2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009, Abbott held $8.3<b>  </b>billion and $7.5 billion, respectively, of such foreign
currency forward exchange contracts.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott has designated foreign denominated
short-term debt as a hedge of the net investment in a foreign subsidiary of
approximately $570 million and approximately $575 million as of March&nbsp;31,
2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009, respectively.&#160;
Accordingly, changes in the fair value of this debt due to changes in
exchange rates are recorded in Accumulated other comprehensive income (loss),
net of tax.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott is a party to interest rate swap
contracts totaling $5.5 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2010 and December&nbsp;31,
2009 to manage its exposure to changes in the fair value of fixed-rate debt due
2011 through 2019.&#160; These contracts are
designated as fair value hedges of the variability of the fair value of
fixed-rate debt due to changes in the long-term benchmark interest rates.&#160; The effect of the hedge is to change a
fixed-rate interest obligation to a variable rate for that portion of the debt.&#160; Abbott records the contracts at fair value
and adjusts the carrying amount of the fixed-rate debt by an offsetting
amount.&#160; No hedge ineffectiveness was
recorded in income in 2010 or 2009 for these hedges.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
following table summarizes the amounts and location of certain derivative
financial instruments as of March&nbsp;31, 2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following
table summarizes the activity for foreign currency forward exchange contracts
designated as cash flow hedges, debt designated as a hedge of net investment in
a foreign subsidiary and the amounts and location of income (expense) and gain
(loss) reclassified into income in the first three months of 2010 and 2009 and
for certain other derivative financial instruments.&#160; The amount of hedge ineffectiveness was not
significant in 2010 and 2009 for these hedges.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The interest rate
swaps are designated as fair value hedges of the variability of the fair value
of fixed-rate debt due to changes in the long-term benchmark interest
rates.&#160; The hedged debt is marked to
market, offsetting the effect of marking the interest rate swaps to market.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The carrying
values and fair values of certain financial instruments as of March&nbsp;31,
2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009 are shown in the table below. The carrying
values of all other financial instruments approximate their estimated fair
values.&#160; The counterparties to financial
instruments consist of select major international financial institutions.&#160; Abbott does not expect any losses from nonperformance
by these counterparties.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="11%" valign="bottom" style="border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;border-left:none;border-right:none;border-top:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:11.56%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5,694</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.68%;">

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#151;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The recorded value of
investments that are valued using significant unobservable inputs did not
change significantly.&#160; Changes in these
values are recorded in Accumulated other comprehensive income.&#160; The fair value of the contingent
consideration was determined based on an independent appraisal adjusted during
the period for the time value of money.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">13<a name="PB_13_083141_8627"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='13',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-05.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Notes to Condensed
Consolidated Financial Statements</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March&nbsp;31,
2010</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited), continued</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note&nbsp;11&nbsp;</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#151;
Goodwill and Intangible Assets</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott recorded
goodwill of approximately $2.1 billion in 2010 related to the acquisitions of
Solvay Pharmaceuticals and STARLIMS Technologies.&#160; In addition, in the first quarter of 2010,
Abbott paid $250 million to Boston Scientific as a result of the approval to
market the <i>Xience V</i> drug-eluting
stent in Japan, resulting in an increase in goodwill.&#160; Abbott recorded goodwill of approximately
$1.7 billion in 2009 related to the acquisitions of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.
and Ibis Biosciences,&nbsp;Inc.&#160; Goodwill
related to the Solvay Pharmaceuticals acquisition was allocated to the
Pharmaceutical Products segment, goodwill related to the Boston Scientific
payment was allocated to the Vascular Products segment and goodwill associated
with the Ibis and STARLIMS acquisitions was allocated to the Diagnostic
Products segment.&#160; Foreign currency
translation adjustments and other adjustments decreased goodwill in the first
three months of 2010 and 2009 by approximately $600 million and $2 million,
respectively.<b>  </b>&#160;The amount of goodwill related to reportable
segments at March&nbsp;31, 2010 was $8.4 billion for the Pharmaceutical
Products segment, $206 million for the Nutritional Products segment, $417
million for the Diagnostic Products segment and $2.7 billion for the Vascular
Products segment.&#160; There were no
reductions of goodwill relating to impairments or disposal of all or a portion
of a business.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
gross amount of amortizable intangible assets, primarily product rights and
technology was $14.9 billion<b>  </b>as of
March&nbsp;31, 2010 and $10.8 billion as of December&nbsp;31, 2009, and
accumulated amortization was $5.4 billion as of March&nbsp;31, 2010 and $5.1
billion as of December&nbsp;31, 2009. Indefinite-lived intangible assets, which
relate to in-process research and development acquired in a business
combination, was approximately $1.2 billion and $610 million at March&nbsp;31,
2010 and December&nbsp;31, 2009, respectively. The estimated annual
amortization expense for intangible assets is approximately $1.4 billion in
2010, $1.5 billion in 2011, $1.4 billion in 2012, $1.0 billion in 2013 and $965
million in 2014.&#160; Amortizable intangible
assets are amortized over 2 to 30&nbsp;years (average 11 years).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Note 12 &#151;
Restructuring Plans</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In
2008, Abbott management approved a plan to streamline global manufacturing
operations, reduce overall costs, and improve efficiencies in Abbott&#146;s core
diagnostic business.&#160; Charges of
approximately $14 million and $9 million were recorded in the first three
months of 2010 and 2009, respectively, relating to this restructuring,
primarily for accelerated depreciation and product transfer costs.&#160; Additional charges will occur through 2011 as
a result of product re-registration timelines required under manufacturing
regulations in a number of countries and product transition timelines.&#160; The following summarizes the activity for
this restructuring: <i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In 2009 and prior
years, Abbott management approved plans to realign its worldwide pharmaceutical
and vascular manufacturing operations and selected domestic and international
commercial and research and development operations in order to reduce
costs.&#160; Charges of $3 million and $9
million were subsequently recorded in the first three months of 2010 and 2009,
respectively, relating to these restructurings, primarily for accelerated
depreciation and product transfer costs.&#160;
The following summarizes the activity for these restructurings: <i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Results of
Operations</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

table details sales by reportable segment for the three months ended March&nbsp;31.&#160; Percent changes are versus the prior year and
are based on unrounded numbers.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The net sales
growth in 2010 reflects unit growth, the favorable effect of a relatively
weaker U.S. dollar and the acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals.&#160; Excluding 4.1 percent of favorable exchange,
net sales increased 10.5 percent in 2010.&#160;
Net sales in 2009 reflect the negative effect of a relatively stronger
U.S. dollar.&#160; Excluding 6.1 percent of
unfavorable exchange, net sales increased 5.4 percent in 2009, which reflects
primarily unit growth.&#160; The relatively
weaker U.S. dollar increased first quarter 2010 Total International sales by
7.4 percent, increased Pharmaceutical Products segment sales by 4.4 percent,
increased Nutritional Product segment sales by 2.6 percent, increased
Diagnostic Products segment sales by 5.5 percent and increased Vascular
Products segment sales by 3.2 percent over the first quarter of 2009.&#160; The relatively stronger U.S. dollar decreased
first quarter 2009 Total International sales by11.1 percent, decreased
Pharmaceutical Products segment sales by 6.6 percent, decreased Nutritional
Product segment sales by 4.2 percent, decreased Diagnostic Products segment
sales by 7.8 percent and decreased Vascular Products segment sales by 4.5
percent over the first quarter of 2008.&#160;&#160;&#160;
Sales growth in the Pharmaceutical Products segment was impacted by the
acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals in the first quarter of 2010.&#160; The sales growth in 2009 for the
Pharmaceutical Products segment and Total U.S. sales in 2009 were impacted by
decreased sales of <i>Depakote </i>due
to generic competition. The sales growth in 2009 for the Vascular Products
segment was impacted by the U.S. launch of the <i>Xience
V </i>drug eluting stent in the third quarter of 2008.&#160; The increase in Other sales in 2010 was
impacted by the acquisition of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc. on February&nbsp;25,
2009.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">15<a name="PB_15_083534_3736"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A comparison of significant product group sales for the three months
ended March&nbsp;31 is as follows.&#160; Percent
changes are versus the prior year and are based on unrounded numbers.</font></p>

  <td width="157" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="8" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="82" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="90" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="8" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="82" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="19" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="90" style="border:none;"></td>
  <td width="7" style="border:none;"></td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Decreased sales of <i>Depakote</i>, due to continued generic
competition, and <i>Lupron</i> decreased
U.S. Specialty product sales in 2010 and was partially offset by increased
sales of <i>HUMIRA</i>.&#160; Decreased sales of <i>Depakote</i> due to generic competition impacted U.S. Specialty
product sales in 2009.&#160; This was
partially offset by the addition of <i>Lupron </i>sales
from the conclusion of the TAP joint venture in April&nbsp;2008.&#160; U.S. sales of <i>Depakote</i> for the first three months of 2010, 2009 and 2008
were $23 million, $110 million and $341 million, respectively.&#160; U.S. Primary Care sales in 2010 were impacted
by increased sales of <i>Niaspan</i> and
the <i>TriCor/Trilipix </i>franchise.&#160; U.S. Primary Care sales in 2009 were impacted
by decreased sales of <i>Omnicef </i>due
to generic competition.&#160; Increased sales
of <i>HUMIRA</i> favorably impacted
International Pharmaceutical sales in both 2010 and 2009.&#160; International sales of <i>HUMIRA</i> for the first three months of 2010
and 2009 were $855 million and $614 million, respectively.&#160; Abbott forecasts full year worldwide <i>HUMIRA</i> sales growth of approximately 20
percent in 2010.&#160; The relatively weaker
U.S. dollar increased International Pharmaceutical sales in 2010 by 7.7 percent
and the relatively stronger U.S. dollar decreased International Pharmaceutical
sales in 2009 by 12.1 percent.&#160; U.S.
Pediatric sales in 2009 were affected by the impact of a decline in the U.S.
infant nutritional market, partially offset by higher market share.&#160; International Pediatric Nutritionals sales
increases in 2010 and 2009 were due primarily to volume growth in developing
countries.&#160; The relatively weaker U.S.
dollar increased International Adult Nutritional sales in 2010 by 7.1 percent
and the relatively stronger U.S. dollar decreased International Adult
Nutritional sales in 2009 by 10.7 percent.&#160;
The relatively weaker U.S. dollar increased Immunochemistry sales in 2010
by 6.0 percent and the relatively stronger U.S. dollar decreased
Immunochemistry sales in 2009 by 8.4 percent.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The gross profit
margin was 56.7 percent for the
first quarter 2010, compared to 56.3 percent for the first quarter 2009.&#160; The increase in the gross profit margin in
2010 was due, in part, to non-recurring charges in 2009 for a delayed product
launch and the discontinuation of a product.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Research and
development expenses increased 12.2 percent in the first quarter 2010 over the
first quarter 2009.&#160; This increase
reflects continued pipeline spending, including programs in vascular devices,
immunology, neuroscience, oncology and Hepatitis C.&#160; The majority of research and development
expenditures are concentrated on pharmaceutical products.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Selling, general
and administrative expenses for the first quarter 2010 increased 4.4 percent
over the first quarter 2009.&#160; This
increase reflects increased selling and marketing support for new and existing
products, including spending for <i>HUMIRA</i>
and <i>Xience V</i>, and inflation.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">16<a name="PB_16_083727_9621"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Business
Acquisitions</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2010,
Abbott acquired Solvay&#146;s pharmaceuticals business (Solvay Pharmaceuticals) for
approximately $6.1 billion, in cash, plus additional payments of up to EUR 100
million per year if certain sales milestones are met in 2011, 2012 and
2013.&#160; Contingent consideration of
approximately $290 million was recorded based on a preliminary valuation.&#160;&#160; The acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals
provides Abbott with a large and complementary portfolio of pharmaceutical
products and expands Abbott&#146;s presence in key global emerging markets.&#160; Abbott acquired control of this business on February&nbsp;15,
2010 and the financial results of the acquired operations are included in these
financial statements beginning on that date.&#160;
Net sales and pretax loss of the acquired operations, including
acquisition and integration expenses, for the first quarter 2010 were
approximately $210 million and $37 million, respectively.&#160; The acquisition was funded with current cash
and short-term investments.&#160; The
preliminary allocation of the fair value of the acquisition is shown in the
table below <i>(in billions of dollars)</i>.&nbsp;
The allocation of the fair value of the acquisition will be finalized when the
valuations are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
