<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquired intangible
assets consist primarily of product rights for currently marketed products and
will be amortized over 2 to 14 years (average of 11 years).&#160; Acquired in-process research and development
will be accounted for as indefinite lived intangible assets until regulatory
approval or discontinuation.&#160; The net
tangible assets acquired consist primarily of trade accounts receivable of
approximately $620 million, inventory of approximately $420 million, property
and equipment of approximately $710 million, net of assumed liabilities,
primarily trade accounts payable, accrued compensation and other liabilities.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following unaudited
pro forma financial information reflects the consolidated results of operations
of Abbott as if the acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals had taken place on January&nbsp;1,
2010 and January&nbsp;1, 2009.&#160; The pro
forma information includes adjustments for amortization of intangible assets
and fair value adjustments to acquisition-date inventory as well as acquisition
and integration expenses.&#160; The pro forma
financial information is not necessarily indicative of the results of
operations as they would have been had the transaction been effected on the
assumed date. (<i>in billions of dollars,
except per share amounts</i>)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

 <tr>
  <td width="52%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:52.6%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.0pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net
  earnings</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.94%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="18%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:18.94%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.0</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.96%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="18%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:18.96%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.3</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.58%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="52%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:52.6%;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In March&nbsp;2010,
Abbott acquired STARLIMS Technologies for approximately $105&nbsp;million, in
cash, net of cash held by STARLIMS, providing Abbott with leading products and
expertise to build its position in laboratory informatics.&#160;&#160; A substantial portion of the fair value of
the acquisition has been allocated to amortizable intangible assets and
goodwill.&#160; The allocation of the fair
value of the acquisition will be finalized when the valuation is completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On April&nbsp;20, 2010,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Facet Biotech Corporation for
approximately $430 million, in cash, net of cash held by Facet.&#160;&#160; The acquisition enhances Abbott&#146;s early- and
mid-stage pharmaceutical pipeline, including a biologic for multiple sclerosis
and compounds that complement Abbott&#146;s oncology program.&#160; A substantial portion of the fair value of
the acquisition will be allocated to acquired in-process research and
development that will be accounted for as an indefinite-lived intangible asset
until regulatory approval or discontinuation.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">17<a name="PB_17_083920_8715"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In February&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired the outstanding shares of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.
(AMO) for approximately $1.4&nbsp;billion in cash, net of cash held by AMO.
Prior to the acquisition, Abbott held a small investment in AMO. Abbott
acquired AMO to take advantage of increasing demand for vision care
technologies due to population growth and demographic shifts and AMO&#146;s premier
position in its field. Abbott acquired control of this business on February&nbsp;25,
2009 and the financial results of the acquired operations are included in these
financial statements beginning on that date. The acquisition was financed with
long-term debt. The allocation of the fair value of the acquisition is shown in
the table below: (<i>dollars in billions</i>)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.4</font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquired intangible
assets consist of established customer relationships, developed technology and
trade names and are amortized over 2 to 30&nbsp;years (average of 15&nbsp;years).
Acquired in-process research and development is accounted for as an
indefinite-lived intangible asset until regulatory approval or discontinuation.
The net tangible assets acquired consist primarily of trade accounts
receivable, inventory, property and equipment and other assets, net of assumed
liabilities, primarily trade accounts payable, accrued compensation and other
liabilities. In addition, subsequent to the acquisition, Abbott repaid
substantially all of the acquired debt of AMO.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In January&nbsp;2009,
Abbott acquired Ibis Biosciences,&nbsp;Inc. (Ibis) for $175&nbsp;million, in
cash, to expand Abbott&#146;s position in molecular diagnostics for infectious
disease. Including a $40&nbsp;million investment in Ibis in 2008, Abbott
acquired 100&nbsp;percent of the outstanding shares of Ibis. A substantial
portion of the fair value of the acquisition has been allocated to goodwill and
amortizable intangible assets, and acquired in-process research and development
that will be accounted for as an indefinite-lived intangible asset until
regulatory approval or discontinuation. The investment in Ibis in 2008 resulted
in a charge to acquired in-process research and development. In connection with
the acquisition, the carrying amount of this investment was revalued to fair
value resulting in recording $33&nbsp;million of income, which is reported as
Other (income) expense, net.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The allocation of the
fair value of the 2009 acquisitions of Visiogen,&nbsp;Inc. and Evalve,&nbsp;Inc.
will be completed when the valuations are completed.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Except for the
acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals, had the above acquisitions taken place
on January&nbsp;1 of the previous year, consolidated net sales and income would
not have been significantly different from reported amounts.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Restructuring
Plans</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In
2008, Abbott management approved a plan to streamline global manufacturing
operations, reduce overall costs, and improve efficiencies in Abbott&#146;s core
diagnostic business.&#160; Charges of
approximately $14 million and $9 million were recorded in the first three
months of 2010 and 2009, respectively, relating to this restructuring,
primarily for accelerated depreciation and product transfer costs.&#160; Additional charges will occur through 2011 as
a result of product re-registration timelines required under manufacturing
regulations in a number of countries and product transition timelines.&#160; The following summarizes the activity for
this restructuring: <i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="63%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:63.34%;">
 <tr>
  <td width="52%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:52.64%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.94%;">
  <p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width="18%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:18.94%;">

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In 2009 and prior
years, Abbott management approved plans to realign its worldwide pharmaceutical
and vascular manufacturing operations and selected domestic and international
commercial and research and development operations in order to reduce
costs.&#160; Charges of $3 million and $9
million were subsequently recorded in the first three months of 2010 and 2009,
respectively, relating to these restructurings, primarily for accelerated depreciation
and product transfer costs.&#160; The
following summarizes the activity for these restructurings: <i>(dollars in millions)</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.76%;">

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="16%" valign="bottom" style="border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;border-left:none;border-right:none;border-top:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:16.7%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">114</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="3%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:3.76%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="border:none;border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.3%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="16%" valign="bottom" style="border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;border-left:none;border-right:none;border-top:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:16.7%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">107</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.48%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Interest Expense
(Income)</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Interest expense
and interest income decreased in the first quarter 2010 compared to 2009
primarily as a result of lower interest rates.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other (income) expense,
net and Net foreign exchange loss (gain)</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Other (income) expense,
net, for the first quarter of 2009 includes the derecognition of a contingent
liability of $797 million and ongoing contractual payments from Takeda
associated with the conclusion of the TAP joint venture, and income from the
recording of certain investments at fair value in connection with business
acquisitions.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net foreign
exchange loss (gain) includes a charge of approximately $86 million for the
impact of the devaluation of the bolivar currency in Venezuela on balance sheet
translation.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Taxes on Earnings</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Taxes on earnings reflect
the estimated annual effective rates and include charges for interest and
penalties. The effective tax rates are less than the statutory U.S. federal
income tax rate principally due to the benefit of lower statutory tax rates and
tax exemptions in several foreign taxing jurisdictions.&#160; As a result of the Patient Protection and
Affordable Care Act and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act which
were signed into law in the first quarter of 2010, Abbott recorded a charge of
approximately $60 million in the first quarter 2010 to reduce deferred tax
assets associated with retiree health care liabilities related to the Medicare Part&nbsp;D
retiree drug subsidy.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Liquidity and
Capital Resources March&nbsp;31, 2010 Compared with December&nbsp;31, 2009</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net cash from
operating activities for the first three months 2010 totaled approximately $1.5
billion. Other, net in Net cash from operating activities for 2010 and 2009
includes the effects of contributions to defined benefit plans of $466 million
and $741 million, respectively.&#160; Abbott
expects annual cash flow from operating activities to continue to exceed Abbott&#146;s
capital expenditures and cash dividends.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The acquisition of
Solvay&#146;s pharmaceuticals business was funded with current cash and short-term
investments.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Working capital
was $2.5 billion at March&nbsp;31, 2010 and $10.3 billion at December&nbsp;31,
2009.&#160; The decrease in working capital
was due to current cash and investments used in the acquisition of Solvay
Pharmaceuticals.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At March&nbsp;31,
2010 Abbott&#146;s long-term debt rating was AA by Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s
Corporation and A1 by Moody&#146;s Investors Service.&#160; Abbott has readily available financial
resources, including unused lines of credit of $6.3 billion that support commercial paper borrowing
arrangements of which a $3.3 billion facility expires in October&nbsp;2010 and
a $3.0 billion facility expires in 2012.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">19<a name="PB_19_084221_9497"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='19',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-07.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL REVIEW</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(continued)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Under a
registration statement filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission in February&nbsp;2009,
Abbott issued $3.0 billion of long-term debt in the first quarter of 2009 that
matures in 2019 and 2039 with interest rates of 5.125 percent and 6.0 percent,
respectively.&#160; Proceeds from this debt
were used to fund the acquisition of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc. and to
repay debt of Advanced Medical Optics,&nbsp;Inc.&#160; In addition, Abbott repaid $1 billion of
long-term notes that were due in February&nbsp;of 2009 using short-term
borrowings.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In October&nbsp;2008,
the board of directors authorized the purchase of up to $5 billion of Abbott&#146;s
common shares from time to time and 14.8 million shares and 14.5 million shares
were purchased under this authorization in the first three months of 2010 and
2009 at a cost of approximately $800 million per quarter for 2010 and 2009.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:-.1pt;line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:0pt;">Legislative Issues</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:-.1pt;line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In the first quarter
2010, the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act and the Health Care and
Education Reconciliation Act (collectively referred to herein as &#147;health care
reform legislation&#148;) were signed into law in the U.S.&#160; Health care reform legislation includes an
increase in the basic Medicaid rebate rate from 15.1% to 23.1% and extends the
rebate to drugs provided through Medicaid managed care organizations.&#160; As a result, Abbott recorded an additional
provision of approximately $60 million against gross sales in the first quarter
2010 for the impact of the rebate charges on first quarter sales as well as
other products in the distribution channel.&#160;
These Medicaid rebate changes will continue to have a negative effect on
the gross profit margin of the Pharmaceutical Products segment in future
quarters.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Beginning in 2013,
health care reform legislation will eliminate the federal income tax deduction
for prescription drug expenses of retirees for which Abbott receives
reimbursement under the Medicare Part&nbsp;D retiree drug subsidy program.&#160; As a result, Abbott recorded a charge of
approximately $60 million in the first quarter 2010 to reduce deferred tax
assets associated with retiree health care liabilities.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In 2011, Abbott will
begin recording the annual fee imposed by health care reform legislation on
companies that sell branded prescription drugs to specified government
programs.&#160; The amount of the annual fee
will be based on the ratio of certain of Abbott&#146;s sales as compared to the
total such sales of all covered entities multiplied by a fixed dollar amount
specified in the legislation by year.&#160; In
2011, additional rebates will be incurred related to the Medicare Part&nbsp;D
coverage gap &#147;donut hole.&#148;&#160; Beginning in
2013, Abbott will record the 2.3% excise tax imposed by health care reform
legislation on the sale of certain medical devices.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s primary
markets are highly competitive and subject to substantial government
regulations throughout the world.&#160; Abbott
expects debate to continue over the availability, method of delivery, and
payment for health care products and services.&#160;
It is not possible to predict the extent to which Abbott or the health
care industry in general might be adversely affected by these factors in the
future.&#160; A more complete discussion of
these factors is contained in Item 1, Business, and Item 1A, Risk Factors, in
the 2009 Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Private Securities
Litigation Reform Act of 1995&nbsp;&#151; A Caution Concerning Forward-Looking
Statements</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Under the safe
harbor provisions of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995,
Abbott cautions investors that any forward-looking statements or projections
made by Abbott, including those made in this document, are subject to risks and
uncertainties that may cause actual results to differ materially from those
projected. Economic, competitive, governmental, technological and other factors
that may affect Abbott&#146;s operations are discussed in Item 1A, Risk Factors, in
the 2009 Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">20<a name="PB_20_084250_5250"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='20',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-07.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.75in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">PART&nbsp;I.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">FINANCIAL
INFORMATION</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.75in;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Item
4.</font></u><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Controls
and Procedures</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Evaluation of disclosure controls and procedures.&#160; </font></i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
Chief Executive Officer, Miles D. White, and Chief Financial Officer, Thomas C.
Freyman, evaluated the effectiveness of Abbott Laboratories&#146; disclosure
controls and procedures as of the end of the period covered by this report, and
concluded that Abbott Laboratories&#146; disclosure controls and procedures were
effective to ensure that information Abbott is required to disclose in the
reports that it files or submits with the Securities and Exchange Commission
under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;) is recorded,
processed, summarized and reported, within the time periods specified in the
Commission&#146;s rules&nbsp;and forms, and to ensure that information required to
be disclosed by Abbott in the reports that it files or submits under the
Exchange Act is accumulated and communicated to Abbott&#146;s management, including
its principal executive officer and principal financial officer, as appropriate
to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Changes in internal control over financial reporting.</font></i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#160; On February&nbsp;15, 2010, Abbott completed
its acquisition of Solvay&#146;s pharmaceuticals business.&#160; During the quarter ended March&nbsp;31, 2010,
there were no other changes in Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial
reporting (as defined in Rule&nbsp;13a-15(f)&nbsp;under the Exchange Act) that
have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect,
Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.75in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">PART&nbsp;II.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">OTHER INFORMATION</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.75in;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Item
1.</font></u><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Legal Proceedings</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott is involved in
various claims, legal proceedings, and investigations, including (as of March&nbsp;31,
2010, except as otherwise indicated) those described below.&nbsp; While it is
not feasible to predict the outcome of such pending claims, proceedings, and
investigations with certainty, management is of the opinion that their ultimate
disposition should not have a material adverse effect on Abbott&#146;s financial
position, cash flows, or results of operations, except for the case filed in April&nbsp;2007
referred to in the second paragraph of Note 4 to Abbott&#146;s financial statements
and the cases and investigations discussed in the third paragraph of such note,
the resolution of which could be material to cash flows or results of
operations.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Several lawsuits filed
against Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc., Solvay Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. (a
company Abbott acquired in February&nbsp;2010) et al. have been consolidated
for pre-trial purposes in the United States District Court for the Northern
District of Georgia under the Multi District Litigation Rules&nbsp;as <i>In re AndroGel Antitrust Litigation</i>, MDL No.&nbsp;2084.&#160; These cases, brought by private plaintiffs
and the Federal Trade Commission (&#147;FTC&#148;), generally allege Solvay&#146;s 2006 patent
litigation involving AndroGel was sham litigation and the patent litigation
settlement agreement and related agreements with three generic companies
violate federal and </font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">21<a name="PB_21_182746_7056"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='21',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-07.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">state antitrust laws and
state consumer protection laws. Plaintiffs generally seek monetary damages
and/or injunctive relief and attorneys&#146; fees.&#160;
MDL 2084 includes:&#160; (a)&nbsp;2
individual plaintiff lawsuits: <i>Rite Aid
Corp. et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals, Inc. et al.</i> and <i>Walgreen Co. et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals, Inc. et
al., </i>both of which were filed in February&nbsp;2009 in the United
States District Court for the Middle District of Pennsylvania; (b)&nbsp;8
purported class actions:&#160; <i>Meijer,&nbsp;Inc. et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.
et al., Rochester Drug Co-Operative,&nbsp;Inc. et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.
et al., </i>and <i>Louisiana Wholesale
Drug Co.,&nbsp;Inc. et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. et al., </i>all
of which were filed in February&nbsp;2009 in the United States District Court
for the Northern District of Georgia;&#160; <i>Stephen L. LaFrance Pharmacy,&nbsp;Inc. et al. v.
Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. et al. </i>and <i>Scurto et al. v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. et
al., </i>both of which were filed in March&nbsp;2009 in the United
States District Court for the District of New Jersey; <i>Fraternal Order of Police v. Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.
et al., </i>filed in April&nbsp;2009 in the United States District Court
for the District of New Jersey; <i>United Food&nbsp;&amp;
Com. Workers Unions&nbsp;&amp; Employ. Midwest Health Benefits Fund et al. v.
Unimed Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. et al., </i>filed in May&nbsp;2009 in
the United States District Court for the District of Minnesota; and <i>Jabo&#146;s Pharmacy,&nbsp;Inc. v. Solvay Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.
et al.,</i> filed in October&nbsp;2009 in the United States District
Court for the Eastern District of Tennessee; and (c)&nbsp;a lawsuit brought by
the FTC, <i>Federal Trade Commission v. Watson
Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc. et al.</i>, filed in January&nbsp;2009 in the
United States District Court for the Central District of California.&#160; In February&nbsp;2010, Solvay&#146;s motion to
dismiss the cases was partially granted and all of the FTC&#146;s claims and all of
the plaintiffs&#146; claims except those alleging sham litigation were
dismissed.&#160; In April&nbsp;2010, Supervalu,&nbsp;Inc.,
an individual plaintiff, filed a lawsuit against Abbott in the United States
District Court for the Northern District of Georgia asserting substantially the
same allegations as the plaintiffs above and seeking monetary damages and/or
injunctive relief and attorneys&#146; fees.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In its 2009 Form&nbsp;10-K,
Abbott reported that litigation is pending in the Regional Court in Dusseldorf,
Germany in which Bayer HealthCare LLC asserts that Humira&#174; infringes Bayer&#146;s
patent and seeks damages, but not an injunction.&#160; In March&nbsp;2010, Abbott filed an action in
the German Federal Patent Court asking that Bayer&#146;s patent be revoked.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In its 2009 Form&nbsp;10-K,
Abbott reported that litigation is pending in the High Court of Ireland, the
District Court in The Hague, Netherlands, and the Regional Court in Dusseldorf,
Germany in which Medinol Limited asserts that certain Abbott stents infringe
various Medinol stent design patents and seeks damages and injunctions, and in the High Court of Justice in the
United Kingdom in which Abbott asserts that its stents do not infringe
Medinol&#146;s patents and seeks a declaration that Medinol&#146;s patents are
invalid.&#160; In February&nbsp;2010,
Medinol appealed the Dutch court&#146;s finding that Abbott&#146;s stents do not infringe
Medinol&#146;s patent.&#160; In March&nbsp;2010,
the Dusseldorf court found that Abbott&#146;s stents do not infringe Medinol&#146;s
European stent design patent, a patent also at issue in the other venues, but
that they do infringe two of Medinol&#146;s German stent design patents.&#160; Medinol
can seek to enforce its right to damages and a provisional injunction in
Germany.&#160; Abbott has the right to appeal
the decision of the Dusseldorf court.&#160; In addition, as previously
reported in Abbott&#146;s 2009 Form&nbsp;10-K, Abbott filed an action in the German
Federal Patent Court asserting that the three Medinol patents at issue are
invalid.&#160; If the German Federal Patent
Court invalidates Medinol&#146;s patents, then any relief granted by the Dusseldorf
court could be rescinded.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">22<a name="PB_22_182807_5335"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='22',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-07.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott is seeking to
enforce its patent rights relating to niacin extended release tablets (a drug
Abbott sells under the trademark Niaspan&#174;).&#160;
In February&nbsp;2010, Abbott filed a case in the United States District
Court for the District of Delaware alleging that Sun Pharmaceutical Industries
Limited&#146;s and Sun Pharma Global FZE&#146;s generic product infringes Abbott&#146;s
patents and seeks declaratory and injunctive relief.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other;text-indent:-.75in;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Item 1A</font></u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Risk Factors</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There have been no material changes in our
risk factors from those disclosed in Abbott&#146;s 2009 Form&nbsp;10-K, except for
the following:</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Changes
in the health care regulatory environment may adversely affect Abbott&#146;s
business.</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Patient Protection and Affordable Care
Act and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act of 2010 were signed
into law on March&nbsp;23, 2010 and March&nbsp;30, 2010, respectively.&#160; A number of the provisions of those laws
require rulemaking action by governmental agencies to implement, which has not
yet occurred.&#160; The laws change access to
health care products and services and create new fees for the pharmaceutical
and medical device industries.&#160; Future
rulemaking could increase rebates, reduce prices or the rate of price increases
for health care products and services, or require additional reporting and
disclosure.&#160; Abbott cannot predict the
timing or impact of any future rulemaking.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">23<a name="PB_23_182855_5796"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='23',FILE='C:\JMS\105939\10-11731-1\task4145264\11731-1-ba-07.htm',USER='105939',CD='Jun  9 02:59 2010' -->

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.75in;"><u><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Item 2.</font></u><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><u>Unregistered

<p style="color:black;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>These
shares include:</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(i)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>the shares deemed
surrendered to Abbott to pay the exercise price in connection with the exercise
of employee stock options - 178,219 in January, 115,229 in February, and 48,715
in March; and</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(ii)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>the shares purchased on
the open market for the benefit of participants in the Abbott Laboratories,
Limited Employee Stock Purchase Plan - 0 in January, 22,500 in February, and
22,500 in March.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">These shares do not include the shares
surrendered to Abbott to satisfy tax withholding obligations in connection with
the vesting of restricted stock or restricted stock units.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 71.9pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-24.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On October&nbsp;13, 2008, Abbott announced
that its board of directors approved the purchase of up to $5 billion of its
common shares, from time to time.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 24.0pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-24.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EXHIBIT
INDEX</font></u></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit 10.1</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ABBOTT LABORATORIES EUROPE</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">WORK CONTRACT</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">BETWEEN THE UNDERSIGNED&nbsp;:</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">ABBOTT LABORATORIES SA, company incorporated under the
Law of Switzerland, with a capital of 50.000 Switzerland Francs, registered
under the Commercial and Company Registry of Zoug, under the number
107&nbsp;927, CH 170.3.015197-9, whose registered office is Neuhofstrasse 23,
6341 Baar, Switzerland.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Whose French branch is located at 10, rue d&#146;Arcueil,
Zone Silic, in Rungis (94), and which is registered under the Commercial and Company
Registry of Cr&#233;teil under the number B 450&nbsp;675&nbsp;905, represented by
Stephen R. Fussell, in his capacity as Senior Vice President, Human Resources,
and Thierry Coosemans, in his capacity as Area Finance Director Western Europe
and Canada.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Hereinafter referred to as &#147;the
company&#148;.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">ON ONE HAND,</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON, born on &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
nationality, residing at &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;,
registered under the Social Security no: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Hereinafter referred to as &#147;Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON&#148;.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">ON THE OTHER HAND,</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">IT HAS BEEN AGREED AS
FOLLOWS:</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 1 : PURPOSE</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company has hired, on the terms set forth below, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON, who accepts, as Executive Vice President Pharmaceutical Products
top-level executive status.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As the Executive Vice President Pharmaceutical
Products, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON is required to perform his duties as
described below.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON is in charge of / responsible
for:</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Managing
Abbott&#146;s financial assets.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Profitably
grow the Pharmaceutical business by leading people and managing key functions
and processes.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Develop
business strategies and assure their implementation. Communicate these strategies
to employees.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Develop
an annual business plan for the Pharmaceutical business and achieve goals that
have been committed to.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Guarantee
that the organization attracts, develops and retains the talent necessary to
grow the business / business success.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Conduct
all business in an ethical manner following Abbott&#146;s Code of Business Conduct.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Take
corrective actions to protect Abbott&#146;s assets, reputation and business. Keep
senior management informed of all important issues that may affect the business.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Understand
the Pharmaceutical business and business environment so as to seek out
opportunities for Abbott and address any potential threats.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-align:left;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The missions as described do not intend to restrict
management&#146;s right to assign or re-assign duties to this job, such change not
being considered as an essential modification of this work contract, as
expressly acknowledged by Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON when signing this employment
contract.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:left;text-indent:1.7pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">shall report to </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">his
superior, currently the Chief Executive Officer </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">or to such person(s)&nbsp;as
directed by the Company.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:left;text-indent:1.7pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For this purpose, the Collective Bargaining Agreement
currently applicable within the company is the one applicable to &#147;Technical
Studies,&#148; Consulting Engineer&#146;s Offices and Consulting Companies&#148; Called
SYNTEC.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This reference to the Collective Bargaining Agreement
is not considered as a substantial condition of this employment contract as
acknowledged by the parties when signing this contract.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr Olivier BOHUON formally declares that he is free
from any commitment towards another company.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON must inform the company of any
changes in his personal status (address, tax residency status, etc) which could
modify his prior statements.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 2 : TRIAL PERIOD</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The present employment contract is concluded for an
unlimited period of time, as from February&nbsp;2010, with no trial period.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The seniority acquired by Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON with
ABBOTT since June&nbsp;1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">st</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">, 2003, is entirely
taken into account for the entitlement to all related benefits.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 3 : PLACE OF WORK</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON&#146;s place of work is at the
premises of the company, which are presently located at 10, rue d&#146;Arcueil, Zone
Silic, Rungis (94) in France.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 4 : BUSINESS TRIPS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the performance of his duties, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON agrees to undertake business trips in France and abroad, and thus to be
away from his home for limited periods of time. For business trips abroad, he
will be compensated as described in Article&nbsp;8.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 5 : WORKING TIME</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON is considered as a top-level
executive in accordance with the provisions of article L. 3111-2 of the Labour
Code, given the nature of this duties, the large freedom which he has been
granted in the organization of this working time and, demonstrated by the high
level of responsibilities and remuneration, he is not subject to the legal
regulations related to the duration of work and is exclusively remunerated for
the successful completion of his assigned tasks.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 6 : PAID HOLIDAYS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON will
be entitled to 25 vacation days per year.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The referenced year for holiday runs from June&nbsp;1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">st</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#160;of the preceding year to May&nbsp;31</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">st</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#160;of the succeeding year.</font></p>
