<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 7 : COMPENSATION</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">7.1 Fixed Compensation</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In compensation for his services, effective March&nbsp;1,
2010, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON shall receive a gross annual remuneration
amounting to 576.388 &#128;uros (five hundred and seventy six thousand three hundred
and eighty eight euros), to be paid in 13 equal monthly instalments. His fixed
compensation will be reviewed and adjusted on an annual basis.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The thirteenth payment will be
paid at the end of November&nbsp;each year.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This remuneration includes the holiday bonus, which is
provided by article 31 of the applicable Collective Bargaining Agreement.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON&#146;s gross annual salary is a
global payment which covers the whole working time required for the expected
performance of his duties, irrespective of the actual hours worked.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">7.2. Variable compensation</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON will receive a variable remuneration according
to the achievement of the targets determined each year by the company,
corresponding to </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">105</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">% of his base
remuneration if established, applicable Company, Division, and individual
performance targets are achieved, as governed by the Performance Incentive
Plan.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">7.3 Tax Equalization</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Given the conditions of performance of his duties and
given the activities of the company, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON is requested to
travel abroad frequently and on periods reaching many weeks in one year.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In order to take into account the time spent abroad
for the needs of and in the interests of the company, and in order to
facilitate compliance with applicable country income tax laws, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON will be covered by the Tax Equalization program as defined in the Abbott
Cross Border Transfer policy now in effect and as changed from time to
time.&#160; Tax preparation services under
this program will be provided by a Company-designated tax consulting firm.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A primary objective of this program is to ensure that
his tax burden while performing his duties abroad will follow tax principles
reasonably similar to those that would have been applicable had he remained in
France.&#160; As an exception to the standard
program elements and only for Tax Equalization calculation purposes, he will be
deemed to benefit in France from an exempted Expatriation Bonus capped for
calculation purposes only at 30%/(1+30%) of his Fixed and Variable Compensation
as defined above.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">It is expressly agreed that Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON
shall record and justify his business travels in an internal document and keep
copies of all receipts of his business trips (expense, receipt, plane tickets,
reports, hotels etc) in order to prove, from a tax equalization standpoint, the
number of days spent outside France and the purposes of these travels.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4<a name="PB_4_220411_2897"></a></font></p>

<div align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='4',FILE='C:\JMS\105568\10-11731-1\task4145984\11731-1-kg.htm',USER='105568',CD='Jun  9 20:03 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 8 : PROFESSIONAL
EXPENSES</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Professional expenses and, in particular, expenses
related to business trips taken by Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON in the exercise of
his duties will be reimbursed upon presentation of supporting receipts, in
accordance with the procedures in force within the company.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 9 : COMPANY CAR</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For the performance of these duties, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON will benefit from a company car, as defined in the Car Policy of the
company.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 10 :&#160; COMPANY BENEFITS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON will be registered to the
complementary retirement scheme of CGIS-CIS CIRCO and ACGME (Groupe Mornay, 5
to 9 rue van Gogh &#151; 75591 PARIS CEDEX 12) and to the provident scheme MERCER
(36, rue Raspail, 92536 Levallois Perret cedex), in force within the company.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">These schemes will be subject
to any legal modification that could be subsequently decided.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 11 : SICKNESS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In the case of incapacity to work due to sickness or
accident, Mr Olivier BOHUON shall advise the company as soon as possible, and
at the latest within 24 hours.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON shall also justify his incapacity
to work by submitting a medical certificate to his management within 48 hours
of his absence at the latest.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 12 : FINANCIAL
PLANNING</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott executives are eligible to participate in the
Abbott Financial Planning Program provided by Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young, JMG
Financial, or Northern Trust. Each of the providers will contact Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON to provide him with information regarding the service they can provide.
Abbott will reimburse him for these services up to the maximum allowable, U.S.
$ 10,000. He will be responsible for any amount over the maximum.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This benefit is taxable to Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON as
imputed income. In any quarter that uses this service, the provider will bill
Abbott directly and Abbott will pay the bill up to the maximum benefit. The
charge for this service will be included in his gross earnings and applicable
tax and social security deductions made from a paycheck prior to the end of
that quarter.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5<a name="PB_5_220435_3020"></a></font></p>

<div align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 13 : PROFESSIONAL
OBLIGATIONS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1 Exclusivity</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Given the confidential nature of his duties as well
his responsibilities and level of remuneration, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON shall
devote the whole of his working time to the performance of his professional
activities to the company and shall not be engaged, for any reason whatsoever,
on his own behalf or on behalf of another individual, in any other professional
activities to the company and shall not be engaged, for any reason whatsoever,
on his own behalf or on behalf of another individual, in any other professional
activity, a fortiori a competing activity, while employed by the company,
except with the prior written consent of the company&#146;s legal representative.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.2 Confidentiality</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON shall keep secret and shall
not at any time during his employment or after termination of his employment
contract, for whatever reason, use, communicate or reveal to any person,
directly or indirectly, for whatever reason, any secret or confidential
information which shall have come to his knowledge during his employment with
the company, except with prior written authorization from the company&#146;s legal
representative.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;Confidential information&#148; includes all information of
whatsoever nature (technical scientific, commercial or other) and, in
particular, all information belonging to the company or any other company of
the group relating to its strategy, its financial situation, its functioning,
its clients, its products, its software programs, its fabrication, marketing
and development plans, business secrets of whatsoever nature.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This commitment will apply to all information relating
to the company&#146;s (or any other company of the group) relationship with clients
and suppliers.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 14 : RESTITUTION</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In case of termination of his employment contract for
whatsoever reason, and on the last day of effective work, Mr.&nbsp;Olivier
BOHUON shall immediately hand over to the company all documents, books,
materials, recordings, correspondence, access codes, computer software,
computer specifications, papers and information (on whatever media and wherever
located) relating to the company&#146;s activity and / or any other company of the
group to which the company belongs.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON shall immediately hand over
any magnetic disk on which information relating to the company&#146;s activity is
stored, and all keys, credit cards and any other means of the company or any
other entity to which the company is linked. He will have to show the evidence
of the good accomplishment of the above obligation.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6<a name="PB_6_220452_7748"></a></font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 15 : TERMINATION</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each party shall have the right to terminate this
employment contract by giving a notice period as determined by the applicable
Collective Bargaining Agreement and at present fixed at 3 months.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">However, this notice period is
not due in case dismissal for serious misconduct or gross misconduct.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE
16: </font></u></b><b><u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">MISCELLANEOUS</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This
Agreement constitutes the entire agreement entered into between the Company and
</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Olivier BOHUON</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">. It
nullifies and supersedes in all respects any other contract or agreement,
whether written or oral, entered into with the Company and/or any affiliated
companies and more generally any arrangements or conventions whatever
previously entered into and relating to the matters dealt in this Agreement by
the parties.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE 17 : APPLICABLE LAW</font></u></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This employment contract shall
be construed and governed by French law.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">French courts will be the only competent courts
regarding the execution, interpretation and termination of this employment
contract.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">In two originals</font></b></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.06%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">NOTE:&#160;&#160; For the purpose of calculating this ratio, (i)&nbsp;earnings
have been calculated by adjusting earnings for taxes on earnings; interest
expense; capitalized interest cost, net of amortization; noncontrolling
interests; and the portion of rentals representative of the interest factor, (ii)&nbsp;Abbott
considers one-third of rental expense to be the amount representing return on
capital, and (iii)&nbsp;fixed charges comprise total interest expense,
including capitalized interest and such portion of rentals.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;punctuation-wrap:simple;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<body lang="EN-US" style="text-justify-trim:punctuation">

<div>

<h6 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit&nbsp;31.1</font></b></h6>

<h6 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></h6>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certification of Chief Executive
Officer</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Required by Rule&nbsp;13a-14(a)&nbsp;(17 CFR
240.13a-14(a))</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">I,
Miles D. White, certify that:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">I
have reviewed this quarterly report on Form&nbsp;10-Q of Abbott Laboratories;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Based
on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a
material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements
made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not
misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Based
on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information
included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial
condition, results of operations and cash flows of Abbott as of, and for, the
periods presented in this report;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s
other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining
disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(e)&nbsp;and
15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in
Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(f)&nbsp;and 15d-15(f)) for Abbott and have:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">a)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Designed
such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and
procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information
relating to Abbott, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to
us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which
this report is being prepared;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">b)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Designed
such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control
over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide
reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the
preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with
generally accepted accounting principles;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">c)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Evaluated
the effectiveness of Abbott&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented
in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure
controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report
based on such evaluation; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">d)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Disclosed
in this report any change in Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial reporting
that occurred during Abbott&#146;s most recent fiscal quarter that has materially
affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, Abbott&#146;s internal
control over financial reporting; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s
other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent
evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to Abbott&#146;s auditors
and the audit committee of Abbott&#146;s board of directors:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">a)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">All
significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of
internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to
adversely affect Abbott&#146;s ability to record, process, summarize and report
financial information; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">b)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Any
fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who
have a significant role in Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div>

<h6 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit&nbsp;31.2</font></b></h6>

<h6 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></h6>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certification of Chief Financial
Officer</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Required by Rule&nbsp;13a-14(a)&nbsp;(17 CFR
240.13a-14(a))</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">I,
Thomas C. Freyman, certify that:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">I
have reviewed this quarterly report on Form&nbsp;10-Q of Abbott Laboratories;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Based
on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a
material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements
made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not
misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Based
on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information
included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial
condition, results of operations and cash flows of Abbott as of, and for, the
periods presented in this report;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s
other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining
disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(e)&nbsp;and
15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in
Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(f)&nbsp;and 15d-15(f)) for Abbott and have:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">a)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Designed
such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and
procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information
relating to Abbott, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to
us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which
this report is being prepared;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">b)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Designed
such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control
over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide
reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the
preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with
generally accepted accounting principles;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">c)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Evaluated
the effectiveness of Abbott&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented
in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure
controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report
based on such evaluation; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">d)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Disclosed
in this report any change in Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial reporting
that occurred during Abbott&#146;s most recent fiscal quarter that has materially
affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, Abbott&#146;s internal
control over financial reporting; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5.</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abbott&#146;s
other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent
evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to Abbott&#146;s auditors
and the audit committee of Abbott&#146;s board of directors:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">a)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">All
significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of
internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to
adversely affect Abbott&#146;s ability to record, process, summarize and report
financial information; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .75in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">b)</font><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Any
fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who
have a significant role in Abbott&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<TYPE>EX-32.1
<SEQUENCE>6
<FILENAME>a10-11731_1ex32d1.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EX-32.1
<TEXT>

<html>

<head>





</head>

<body lang="EN-US" style="text-justify-trim:punctuation">

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 3.0in;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit&nbsp;32.1</font></b></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 3.0in;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certification
Pursuant To</font></b></h2>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">18 U.S.C. Section&nbsp;1350</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">As Adopted Pursuant To</font></b></p>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Section&nbsp;906
of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002</font></b></h2>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></h2>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In connection with the Quarterly Report of Abbott Laboratories (the &#147;Company&#148;)
on Form&nbsp;10-Q for the period ended March&nbsp;31, 2010 as filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;Report&#148;), I, Miles D. White, Chairman
of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of the Company, certify, pursuant to
18 U.S.C. &#167; 1350, as adopted pursuant to &#167; 906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002,
that:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The Report fully complies with the
requirements of section 13(a)&nbsp;or 15(d)&nbsp;of the Securities Exchange Act
of 1934; and</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The information contained in the Report fairly
presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of
operations of the Company.</p>

<h4 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.5in;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit&nbsp;32.2</font></b></h4>

<h4 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.5in;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></h4>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Certification
Pursuant To</font></b></h2>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">18 U.S.C. Section&nbsp;1350</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">As Adopted Pursuant To</font></b></p>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Section&nbsp;906
of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002</font></b></h2>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;text-indent:0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></h2>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In connection with the Quarterly Report of
Abbott Laboratories (the &#147;Company&#148;) on Form&nbsp;10-Q for the period ended March&nbsp;31,
2010 as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;Report&#148;), I,
Thomas C. Freyman, Executive Vice President, Finance and Chief Financial
Officer of the Company, certify, pursuant to 18 U.S.C. &#167; 1350, as adopted
pursuant to &#167; 906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, that:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

requirements of section 13(a)&nbsp;or 15(d)&nbsp;of the Securities Exchange Act
of 1934; and</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The information contained in the Report fairly

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 1 &amp;#151; Basis of Presentation&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;The accompanying unaudited, condensed consolidated financial statements have been prepared pursuant to rules&amp;nbsp;and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission and, therefore, do not include all information and footnote disclosures normally included in audited financial statements.&amp;nbsp; However, in the opinion of management, all adjustments (which include only normal adjustments) necessary to present fairly the results of operations, financial position and cash flows have been made.&amp;nbsp; It is suggested that these statements be read in conjunction with the financial statements included in Abbott&amp;#146;s Annual Report on Form&amp;nbsp;10-K for the year ended December&amp;nbsp;31, 2009.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

  <us-gaap:OtherIncomeAndOtherExpenseDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="D2010Q1">&lt;table style="font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',times,serif;"&gt;

&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 2 &amp;#151; Supplemental Financial Information&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Unvested restricted stock units that contain non-forfeitable rights to dividends are treated as participating securities and are included in the computation of earnings per share under the two-class method.&amp;nbsp; Under the two-class method, net earnings are allocated between common shares and participating securities.&amp;nbsp; Net earnings allocated to common shares for the three months ended March&amp;nbsp;31, 2010 and 2009 were $1.001 billion and $1.436 billion, respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Other (income) expense, net, for the first quarter of 2009 includes the derecognition of a contingent liability of $797 million and ongoing contractual payments from Takeda associated with the conclusion of the TAP joint venture, and income from the recording of certain investments at fair value in connection with business acquisitions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Net foreign exchange loss (gain) includes a charge of approximately $86 million for the impact of the devaluation of the bolivar currency in Venezuela on balance sheet translation.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Other, net in Net cash from operating activities for 2010 and 2009 includes the effects of contributions to defined benefit plans of $466 million and $741 million, respectively, and to the post-employment medical and dental benefit plans of $66 million and $13 million, respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;The judgment entered by the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas against Abbott in its litigation with New York University and Centocor,&amp;nbsp;Inc. requires Abbott to secure the judgment in the event that its appeal to the Federal Circuit court is unsuccessful in overturning the district court&amp;#146;s decision.&amp;nbsp; In the first quarter of 2010, Abbott deposited $1.87 billion with an escrow agent and considers these assets to be restricted.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;The components of long-term investments as of March&amp;nbsp;31, 2010 and December&amp;nbsp;31, 2009 are as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right" align="right"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;1,133&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

</us-gaap:OtherIncomeAndOtherExpenseDisclosureTextBlock>
  <us-gaap:IncomeTaxDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="D2010Q1">&lt;table style="font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',times,serif;"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 3 &amp;#151; Taxes on Earnings&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Taxes on earnings reflect the estimated annual effective rates and include charges for interest and penalties. The effective tax rates are less than the statutory U.S. federal income tax rate principally due to the benefit of lower statutory tax rates and tax exemptions in several foreign taxing jurisdictions.&amp;nbsp; As a result of the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act which were signed into law in the first quarter of 2010, Abbott recorded a charge of approximately $60 million in the first quarter 2010 to reduce deferred tax assets associated with retiree health care liabilities related to the Medicare Part&amp;nbsp;D retiree drug subsidy.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
</us-gaap:IncomeTaxDisclosureTextBlock>
  <us-gaap:CommitmentsAndContingenciesDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="D2010Q1">&lt;table style="font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',times,serif;"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 4 &amp;#151; Litigation and Environmental Matters&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;Abbott has been identified as a potentially responsible party for investigation and cleanup costs at a number of locations in the United States and Puerto Rico under federal and state remediation laws and is investigating potential contamination at a number of company-owned locations.&amp;nbsp; Abbott has recorded an estimated cleanup cost for each site for which management believes Abbott has a probable loss exposure.&amp;nbsp; No individual site cleanup exposure is expected to exceed $3&amp;nbsp;million, and the aggregate cleanup exposure is not expected to exceed $15&amp;nbsp;million.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;There are a number of patent disputes with third parties who claim Abbott&amp;#146;s products infringe their patents.&amp;nbsp; In April&amp;nbsp;2007, New York University (NYU) and Centocor,&amp;nbsp;Inc. filed a lawsuit in the Eastern District of Texas asserting that &lt;i&gt;HUMIRA&lt;/i&gt; infringes a patent co-owned by NYU and Centocor and exclusively licensed to Centocor.&amp;nbsp; In June&amp;nbsp;2009, a jury found that Abbott had willfully infringed the patent and awarded NYU and Centocor approximately $1.67 billion in past compensatory damages.&amp;nbsp; In October&amp;nbsp;2009, the district court overturned the jury&amp;#146;s finding that Abbott&amp;#146;s infringement was willful, but denied Abbott&amp;#146;s request to overturn the jury&amp;#146;s verdict on validity, infringement, and damages.&amp;nbsp; In December&amp;nbsp;2009, the district court issued a final judgment and award
ed the plaintiffs an additional $175 million in prejudgment interest.&amp;nbsp; Abbott has appealed the jury&amp;#146;s verdict.&amp;nbsp; Abbott is confident in the merits of its case and believes that it will prevail on appeal.&amp;nbsp; As a result, no reserves have been recorded in this case.&amp;nbsp; Abbott&amp;#146;s acquisition of Kos Pharmaceuticals Inc. resulted in the assumption of various cases and investigations and Abbott has recorded a reserve.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;There are several civil actions pending brought by individuals or entities that allege generally that Abbott and numerous pharmaceutical companies reported false or misleading pricing information relating to the average wholesale price of certain pharmaceutical products in connection with federal, state and private reimbursement.&amp;nbsp; Civil actions have also been brought against Abbott, and in some cases other members of the pharmaceutical industry, by state attorneys general seeking to recover alleged damages on behalf of state Medicaid programs.&amp;nbsp; In May&amp;nbsp;2006, Abbott was notified that the U.S. Department of Justice intervened in a civil whistle-blower lawsuit alleging that Abbott inflated prices for Medicaid and Medicare reimbursable drugs.&amp;nbsp; Abbott has settled a few of the cases and recorded reserves for its estimated losses in a few other 
cases, however, Abbott is unable to estimate the range or amount of possible loss for the remaining cases, and no loss reserves have been recorded for them.&amp;nbsp; Many of the products involved in these cases are Hospira products.&amp;nbsp; Hospira, Abbott&amp;#146;s former hospital products business, was spun off to Abbott&amp;#146;s shareholders in 2004. Abbott retained liability for losses that result from these cases and investigations to the extent any such losses both relate to the sale of Hospira&amp;#146;s products prior to the spin-off of Hospira and relate to allegations that were made in such pending and future cases and investigations that were the same as allegations existing at the date of the spin-off.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;Within the next year, legal proceedings may occur that may result in a change in the estimated reserves recorded by Abbott.&amp;nbsp; For its legal proceedings and environmental exposures, except as noted above, Abbott estimates the range of possible loss to be from approximately $190 million to $315 million.&amp;nbsp; The recorded reserve balance at March&amp;nbsp;31, 2010 for these proceedings and exposures was approximately $235 million.&amp;nbsp; These reserves represent management&amp;#146;s best estimate of probable loss, as defined by&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style="COLOR: windowtext" color="black"&gt;FASB ASC No.&amp;nbsp;450, &amp;#147;Contingencies.&amp;#148;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;While it is not feasible to predict the outcome of all such proceedings and exposures with certainty, management believes that their ultimate disposition should not have a material adverse effect on Abbott&amp;#146;s financial position, cash flows, or results of operations, except for the cases and investigations discussed in the third paragraph and the patent case discussed in the second paragraph of this footnote, the resolution of which could be material to cash flows or results of operations.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
</us-gaap:CommitmentsAndContingenciesDisclosureTextBlock>
  <us-gaap:PostemploymentBenefitsDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="D2010Q1">&lt;table style="font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',times,serif;"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;Retirement plans consist of defined benefit, defined contribution, and medical and dental plans.&amp;nbsp; Net cost for the three months ended March&amp;nbsp;31 for Abbott&amp;#146;s major defined benefit plans and post-employment medical and dental benefit plans is as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; COLOR: black"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" color="black" size="2"&gt;Abbott funds its domestic defined benefit plans according to IRS funding limitations.&amp;nbsp; In the first quarters of 2010 and 2009, $466 million and $741 million, respectively, was contributed to defined benefit plans and $66 million and $13 million, respectively, was contributed to the post-employment medical and dental benefit plans.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right" align="right"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;(93&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 2.5%; PADDING-TOP: 0in" valign="bottom" width="2%"&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 12%; PADDING-TOP: 0in" valign="bottom" width="12%" colspan="2"&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: right" align="right"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;44&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

  <us-gaap:SegmentReportingDisclosureTextBlock contextRef="D2010Q1">&lt;table style="font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',times,serif;"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 7 &amp;#151; Segment Information&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Abbott&amp;#146;s principal business is the discovery, development, manufacture and sale of a broad line of health care products.&amp;nbsp; Abbott&amp;#146;s products are generally sold directly to retailers, wholesalers, hospitals, health care facilities, laboratories, physicians&amp;#146; offices and government agencies throughout the world.&amp;nbsp; Abbott&amp;#146;s reportable segments are as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Pharmaceutical Products&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt" size="2"&gt; &amp;#151; Worldwide sales of a broad line of pharmaceuticals.&amp;nbsp; For segment reporting purposes, three pharmaceutical divisions are aggregated and reported as the Pharmaceutical Products segment.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Nutritional Products&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt" size="2"&gt; &amp;#151; Worldwide sales of a broad line of adult and pediatric nutritional products.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Diagnostic Products&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt" size="2"&gt; &amp;#151; Worldwide sales of diagnostic systems and tests for blood banks, hospitals, commercial laboratories and alternate-care testing sites.&amp;nbsp; For segment reporting purposes, three diagnostic divisions are aggregated and reported as the Diagnostic Products segment.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Vascular&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt" size="2"&gt;  &lt;i&gt;Products&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#151; Worldwide sales of coronary, endovascular, vessel closure and other products.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Abbott&amp;#146;s underlying accounting records are maintained on a legal entity basis for government and public reporting requirements.&amp;nbsp; Segment disclosures are on a performance basis consistent with internal management reporting.&amp;nbsp; Intersegment transfers of inventory are recorded at standard cost and are not a measure of segment operating earnings.&amp;nbsp; The cost of some corporate functions and the cost of certain employee benefits are charged to segments at predetermined rates that approximate cost.&amp;nbsp; Remaining costs, if any, are not allocated to segments. &lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;For acquisitions prior to 2006, substantially all intangible assets and related amortization are not allocated to segments.&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/b&gt;The following segment information has been prepared in accordance with the internal accounting policies of A
bbott, as described above, and are not presented in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles applied to the consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 8 &amp;#151; Incentive Stock Programs&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;In the first three months of 2010, Abbott granted 1,510,300 stock options, 163,395 replacement stock options, 1,734,700 restricted stock awards and 5,611,368 restricted stock units under these programs.&amp;nbsp; At March&amp;nbsp;31, 2010, approximately 200&amp;nbsp;million shares were reserved for future grants.&amp;nbsp; Information regarding the number of options outstanding and exercisable at March&amp;nbsp;31, 2010 is as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;Note 9 &amp;#151; Business Acquisitions&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;In February&amp;nbsp;2010, Abbott acquired Solvay&amp;#146;s pharmaceuticals business (Solvay Pharmaceuticals) for approximately $6.1 billion, in cash, plus additional payments of up to EUR 100 million per year if certain sales milestones are met in 2011, 2012 and 2013.&amp;nbsp; Contingent consideration of approximately $290 million was recorded based on a preliminary valuation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The acquisition of Solvay Pharmaceuticals provides Abbott with a large and complementary portfolio of pharmaceutical products and expands Abbott&amp;#146;s presence in key global emerging markets.&amp;nbsp; Abbott acquired control of this business on February&amp;nbsp;15, 2010 and the financial results of the acquired operations are included in these financial statements beginning on that date.&amp;nbsp; Net sales and pretax loss of the acquired operations, including acquisitio
n and integration expenses, for the first quarter 2010 were approximately $210 million and $37 million, respectively.&amp;nbsp; The acquisition was funded with current cash and short-term investments.&amp;nbsp; The preliminary allocation of the fair value of the acquisition is shown in the table below &lt;i&gt;(in billions of dollars)&lt;/i&gt;.&amp;nbsp; The allocation of the fair value of the acquisition will be finalized when the valuations are completed.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; punctuation-wrap: simple"&gt;&lt;font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman" size="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
